<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-06T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="830" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d830">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">361.11/3622: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-06T18:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            6, 1920—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received December
                                    7—11:58 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>622. Polish Government has expressed willingness to discuss with
                                Soviets delegation, Riga, exchange Americans in Soviet Russia. Young
                                has informally furnished list of names and suggests I ask Department
                                as to how far matter should be pressed. Request instructions.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>